## Query Cache Management

### Invalidate Queries After Mutations
```typescript
// In useApiPost, specify queries to invalidate:
useApiPost(
  url,
  [
    { name: 'articles', type: 'all' },
    { name: 'articles', type: 'detail' }
  ]
);
```

### Manual Cache Control
```typescript
import { QueryClient } from '@/services/queryClient';
import { queryKeys } from '@/services/queryKeys';

const queryClient = QueryClient.getInstance();

// Invalidate specific query
queryClient?.invalidateQueries({
  queryKey: [queryKeys.articles.all]
});

// Refetch specific query
queryClient?.refetchQueries({
  queryKey: [queryKeys.articles.detail, articleId]
});

// Clear all cache
queryClient?.clear();
```

## Performance Optimization

### 1. Cache Configuration
```typescript
// Default settings in useApiGet
gcTime: 2 * 60 * 1000, // 2 minutes (garbage collection)
refetchOnMount: 'always', // or true, false
```

### 2. Conditional Fetching
```typescript
useApiGet(
  url,
  'articles',
  'detail',
  id,
  params,
  'always',
  2 * 60 * 1000,
  !!id // Only fetch when ID exists
);
```

### 3. Optimistic Updates
```typescript
const mutation = useApiPost(url, queries);

mutation.mutate(data, {
  onMutate: async (newData) => {
    // Cancel outgoing refetches
    await queryClient.cancelQueries({ queryKey: ['articles'] });

    // Snapshot previous value
    const previousData = queryClient.getQueryData(['articles']);

    // Optimistically update
    queryClient.setQueryData(['articles'], (old: any) => [...old, newData]);

    return { previousData };
  },
  onError: (err, newData, context) => {
    // Rollback on error
    queryClient.setQueryData(['articles'], context?.previousData);
  },
});
```

